            <title>SDT, Ludeca Form Partnership</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	SDT recently announced the appointment of Ludeca as the exclusive distributor for its portable and online ultrasound condition monitoring technologies in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;This strategic partnership is a logical step for two companies whose philosophies are already so closely aligned,&amp;quot; said Allan Rienstra, director of business development for SDT. &amp;quot;Both SDT and Ludeca are approved Reliability Leadership Institute (RLI) Mapped Services and Training (MSAT) providers. This partnership will deliver significant value to customers through the leveraging of Ludeca&amp;#39;s knowledge and experience.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	A leading supplier of alignment, vibration and condition monitoring systems to industry, Ludeca is a premier provider of reliability solutions and technologies. The company&amp;#39;s headquarters are located in Miami, Florida.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	SDT develops ultrasound technology that provides industry with a better understanding about the health of their factory. Its ultrasound condition monitoring solutions are designed to predict failures, control energy costs and improve product quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We are excited by the opportunity to affiliate ourselves with a global ultrasound technology leader such as SDT,&amp;quot; said Frank Seidenthal, president of Ludeca. &amp;quot;SDT&amp;#39;s reputation for producing quality, dependable ultrasound solutions marries well with our vision to enhance our asset condition management product palette.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.sdthearmore.com"&gt;www.sdthearmore.com&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="http://www.ludeca.com"&gt;www.ludeca.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/ultrasonic_inspection/~4/a78tkFearEQ" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
