				&lt;img alt="" border="0" src="http://files.gereports.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/gold-bar.jpg" style="margin-bottom: 1em" /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: bold"&gt;Golden Eye:&lt;/span&gt; The ultrasound technology being used to scan gold bars is part of an entire family of scanning and monitoring technologies across all of GE&amp;rsquo;s businesses. Just a few include medical imaging, robotic scanners that travel through oil and gas pipelines, remote monitoring of jet engines, cameras that peer inside of jet and locomotive engines to inspect for wear, and railroad technologies that track speed and manage fleets to maximize efficiency.&lt;/td&gt;
